        <div class="column">
          <div class="content">
          <img src="/Assets/images/ux:ui.jpg" alt="ux-ui-image" style="width:100%">
            <h3>UX/UI</h3>
            <p>UX (User Experience) and UI (User Interface) design are closely related disciplines that focus on creating user-centric digital experiences. UX design involves understanding user behaviors, needs, and motivations to design products or services that are easy to use, efficient, and enjoyable. UI design, on the other hand, focuses on the visual and interactive elements of a digital interface, including buttons, menus, icons, and layout. UX/UI designers work together to ensure that the overall experience is intuitive, visually pleasing, and meets the needs of the target audience.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column">
          <div class="content">
          <img src="/Assets/images/software.jpg" alt="software-development-image" style="width:100%">
            <h3>Software Development</h3>
            <p>Software development refers to the process of creating, designing, and programming software applications. It involves writing code, testing, debugging, and maintaining software systems. Software developers use programming languages and frameworks to build applications for various platforms, such as desktop, web, and mobile. It involves understanding the requirements to deliver high-quality software solutions that meet user needs. </p>
          </div>
